description._content: ID: add_ms_37768_fblefr Title: Lothaire Psalter Provenance: Carolingian Empire; 9th century Caption: In the centre, a silver gilt medallion, probably representing the Emperor Lothaire, in profile, wearing a crown or helmet of primitive pattern. This is enclosed in a framework of silver-gilt with flat conventional leaf pattern, probably added between the 10th and 11th centuries Language: Latin Source identifier: Add. 37768, binding British Library Shelfmark: Add. 37768 If you wish to purchase a high quality copy of this image, please place an order at Images Online imagesonline.bl.uk.
